{"name":"Alter Environment","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The enemy can smash walls, reveal pits, trigger traps, produce fog, or apply any number of other environmental effects that don&rsquo;t affect the characters themselves. Such abilities generally apply disadvantage to certain rolls, or force reactions (e.g., when smashing down a building with the PCs inside)</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"6ixxcKsRrkAKYOhb"}
{"name":"Knockback","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>On a 9- to defend, the PC is forcibly moved around by the enemy to a reasonable location within short range.</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"7GAkPxECNCW9D0Oy"}
{"name":"Gargantuan","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The enemy is massively large, large enough for one or multiple PCs to stand atop it. Some gargantuan creatures are so large that they can house a structure or two on their back.</p>\n<p>Such enemies are actually constructs of multiple enemies added together, each able to be targeted and defeated. If one such component is central to the creature&rsquo;s function (e.g., its head), destroying it will often kill all of the connected bits.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Example: The Gargantuan Golden Wyrm of Akzoth is actually made of four enemies&mdash; its head, body, wings, and tail. Though they are part of the same creature, each of these enemies has its own set of abilities. The wings grant permission to fly, the claws grant pin, the tail trip, and the head fire breath.</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"Cak7QM5adPYCvxvg"}
{"name":"Poison","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>If an attack deals damage to a PC, the PC rolls to resist the poison. On a 7-9, the PC takes the injury tag [poisoned], which can cause slowness, vomiting, or dizziness. On a 6-, the PC takes damage each turn equal to the enemy damage mod. If they hit 0 HP, the [poison] injury tag becomes permanent until cured.&nbsp;</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"EpbK5ZYpITQSNLtk"}
{"name":"Breath / Blast / Gas","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The enemy attacks a wide area in front of it or in a blast zone. The more area covered, the weaker its effect.</p>\n<p>Examples:&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Blinding gas: disadvantage to perception and combat&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Flame breath: deal damage mod to all in zone, AP2</li>\n<li>Forceful gale: strong gust of air that knocks PCs prone and prevents missile attacks</li>\n</ul>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"Gyp8VElh0PSe9OM9"}
{"name":"Special movement","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This enemy can fly, burrow, swim, teleport, phase, or move in another special way. Each form of special movement requires a speed and counts as its own ability.</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"HdCKGiU8CAzGmxOu"}
{"name":"Magical Healing","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>restore 3 HP to one target, short range</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"L9W17r81qahD18jE"}
{"name":"Stun","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Any PC that takes damage from this enemy takes the temporary injury tag [stunned], and loses their next action. Each PC can only be [stunned] once in this way</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"MVT3IPaP2iv7VjVy"}
{"name":"Swarm","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>An aggregate of many smaller enemies collected into one. Swarms are treated as a regular enemy except that their armor and damage modifier depend upon how &ldquo;full&rdquo; they are. As they take damage, their armor and damage modifier decrease in proportion. Spray attacks are treated as armor piercing against a swarm. Once a swarm has been reduced to one-quarter its original HP, it breaks into several individual creatures.&nbsp;</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"NjJYqwnPY0JNFkbH"}
{"name":"Hit and Run","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>On a 9- to defend, the enemy deals damage as normal and then moves to a range relevant to its speed (usually short range).</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"O1GiOSgrXfpY6DIP"}
{"name":"Pin","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>On a 9- to defend, the PC cannot move until they succeed at another roll or until the enemy is suffi ciently distracted or damaged.</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"O90apLf6kPXTSpIs"}
{"name":"Immune to [type]","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Select a type of weapon, attack, or magic. The enemy is completely immune to this.</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"QgAAWLDEau36ZBoI"}
{"name":"Resistant to [type]","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Select a type of weapon, attack, or magic. The enemy has +1 armor against this.&nbsp;</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"TWGEr5t6TViJiYJK"}
{"name":"Paralysis","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>On a 7-9 to defend, the PC is temporarily [paralyzed], which reduces speed by -1 per turn until -7. During this time, the PC struggles to fi ght and make physical actions. On a 6- to defend, the PC immediately goes to -7 speed. If they reach 0 HP, the [paralyzed] injury tag becomes permanent.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"ZUxdkqR1S5lMhUsI"}
{"name":"Trip","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>On a 9- to defend, the PC is knocked prone and is vulnerable to a more lethal strike. Additionally, the PC can&rsquo;t move except to crawl or stand up, and attacks at disadvantage until standing.</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"iIWWKKq0Qo8nfjd0"}
{"name":"Drain","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>On a hit, the PC takes 1 damage per turn (ignores armor) until healed or cured</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"imP92H4OmLuxF93a"}
{"name":"Multiattack N","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This enemy can attack N times in one action, either targeting the same PC multiple times, or targeting many of them within range. Most such enemies have multiattack 2, very powerful ones 3, and nemeses 4.&nbsp;</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"md47Uo8FsWoykHT0"}
{"name":"Invisible","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Impossible to detect the enemy by nonmagical visual means.</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"mvqVqRl7vJiMeB7n"}
{"name":"Reaction Attack","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This enemy gets an immediate attack as a reaction to any PC who attacks them and rolls a 7-9.&nbsp;</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"qrEKWd0xBm0llf2J"}
{"name":"Swallow","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>On a 7-9 to defend, the PC is caught in the enemy&rsquo;s jaws, and can&rsquo;t move but can still attack. On a 6-, the PC is swallowed and takes damage equal to the enemy&rsquo;s damage mod each turn until they extricate.</p>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"t9edudc5ESPqhYOS"}
{"name":"Critical weakness","type":"technique","img":"systems/vagabonds/assets/ifrit.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The enemy cannot die or resurrects (or may not even be able to take any form of damage) unless its critical weakness is exploited. This weakness must be telegraphed to the party, or must be something known to those who are learned about this enemy.</p>\n<p>Examples:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Wraiths must be captured within a prison ward spell</li>\n<li>Zombies must be decapitated or burned</li>\n<li>Liches must have their phylactery destroyed</li>\n</ul>","label":"","value":"","corrupted":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"yWLioonpS57KCFBR":3},"flags":{},"_id":"tjIQCy50GUY0Dr1B"}
